\f0\b\fs24 \cf2 \cb3 General issues with running MuseScore Studio on iOS:
\f1\b0 \
\
The good news: Our build of MSS for iOS launches and runs. \
\
It seems to use a modest amount of both CPU and memory when running and does not appear to leak any resources that would cause iOS to want to kill the app after a 12-hour test. The UI looks good, all the expected views appear to be there except for the menu bar. \
\
The app can even be built and run on an actual iOS device, in this case an iPad 13" running iOS 16. (Instructions for that build are forthcoming.)\
\
The bad news: the app has significant issues. Loads of them.\
\
The main one is that the app is expecting mouse clicks, not touches, and so frequently does not respond as expected. The other is that when new windows are opened or closed, frequently nothing happens until you hit the Home button then click on MSS to bring it forward again. This is likely similarly due to the app expecting a desktop window system rather than the single-fullscreen-window of iOS.\
\
The app cannot yet create a new document - that dialog will freeze. OTOH, the app can open documents from iCloud, and this is how we have sent test documents to it.\
\
