\f0\b Major changes needed for iOS:
\f1\b0 \
\
We need to completely rethink the user interaction model for iOS devices. Fingers are huge for editing a score.\
We will need to make layout files (Main.qml and friends) for iPhone and iPad devices, and set that up in guiapp.cpp.\
App needs to respond to device rotation.\
Shortcuts need to be replaced by gestures. Pinch gesture will probably be used almost everywhere. OTOH, if there is a (Bluetooth) keyboard attached to the device, the keystroke shortcuts should be respected.\
We need to make the DevTools view fit, it is too wide.\
Widget dialogs have no frame, and should they? Is it presuming a Mac window outline and shadow?\
Do we want to support special input for the Apple Pencil? If so, the app still needs to be fully functional without it.\
\
Fixed:\
\uc0\u8730  Any plugins that require running code (as opposed to executing a script) will need to be built in to the app, as iOS does not permit an app to load and execute code. We may be OK on this one, we don\'92t host any audio processing plugins (such as VST) which require running native code.\
\
The menu bar on the Mac includes things that aren\'92t accessible in iOS. As stated, we will need a full menu bar implementation for iOS. And it seems that the main window on iOS leaves room at the top, \strike \strikec2 perhaps it thinks there is a menu bar there because the app always has one on the desktop platforms?\strike0\striked0  No, this is where the view thinks it has the Mac window header. Hmm, maybe we can make use of the Linux or Windows on-the-window menu bar for iOS. This is in appmenumodel.cpp, and we can make an IOSPlatformTheme for things like indicating that there is no global menu bar.\
